#. <section class="sutta" id="an7.52"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an7.52:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 7"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.52:0.2"
msgid "5. Mahāyaññavagga"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an7.52:0.3"
msgid "52. Dānamahapphalasutta"
msgstr ""

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an7.52:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā campāyaṃ viharati gaggarāya pokkharaṇiyā tīre."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sambahulā campeyyakā upāsakā yena āyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;"
" upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. "
"Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho campeyyakā upāsakā āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""

#. VAR: bhante → bhante sāriputta (bj)
msgctxt "an7.52:1.3"
msgid "“cirassutā no, bhante, bhagavato sammukhā dhammīkathā."
msgstr ""

#. VAR: bhagavato sammukhā dhammiṃ kathaṃ → bhagavato santikā dhammiṃ kathaṃ (bj) | bhagavato dhammiṃ kathaṃ (s1-3) | bhagavato sammukhā dhammikathaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "an7.52:1.4"
msgid ""
"Sādhu mayaṃ, bhante, labheyyāma bhagavato sammukhā dhammiṃ kathaṃ "
"savanāyā”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:1.5"
msgid "“Tenahāvuso, tadahuposathe āgaccheyyātha, "
msgstr ""

#. VAR: bhagavato sammukhā → bhagavato santike (s1-3)
msgctxt "an7.52:1.6"
msgid "appeva nāma labheyyātha bhagavato sammukhā dhammiṃ kathaṃ savanāyā”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:1.7"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho campeyyakā upāsakā āyasmato sāriputtassa paṭissutvā "
"uṭṭhāyāsanā āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkamiṃsu."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an7.52:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho campeyyakā upāsakā tadahuposathe yenāyasmā sāriputto "
"tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ "
"aṭṭhaṃsu."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:2.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto tehi campeyyakehi upāsakehi saddhiṃ yena bhagavā "
"tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. "
"Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

# BB seems to omit the repeated tadisamyeva in his translation, which weakens the force of the question: “exactly the same kind of gift …”
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.60"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an7.52:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Siyā nu kho, bhante, idhekaccassa tādisaṃyeva dānaṃ dinnaṃ na mahapphalaṃ "
"hoti na mahānisaṃsaṃ;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:3.2"
msgid ""
"siyā pana, bhante, idhekaccassa tādisaṃyeva dānaṃ dinnaṃ mahapphalaṃ hoti "
"mahānisaṃsan”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:3.3"
msgid ""
"“Siyā, sāriputta, idhekaccassa tādisaṃyeva dānaṃ dinnaṃ na mahapphalaṃ hoti "
"na mahānisaṃsaṃ;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:3.4"
msgid ""
"siyā pana, sāriputta, idhekaccassa tādisaṃyeva dānaṃ dinnaṃ mahapphalaṃ hoti "
"mahānisaṃsan”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:3.5"
msgid ""
"“Ko nu kho, bhante, hetu ko paccayo yena midhekaccassa tādisaṃyeva dānaṃ "
"dinnaṃ na mahapphalaṃ hoti na mahānisaṃsaṃ;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:3.6"
msgid ""
"ko nu kho, bhante, hetu ko paccayo yena midhekaccassa tādisaṃyeva dānaṃ "
"dinnaṃ mahapphalaṃ hoti mahānisaṃsan”ti?"
msgstr ""

# I don’t think BB’s “looking for rewards” is quite right for sannidhipekho. A reward is something that you get, but this refers to keeping what you’ve got. sannidhi means to store up, and as the next phrase makes clear, it means you’re not really giving so much as investing. I think this is a significant difference between this and the teaching on kamma.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
#. VAR: sāpekho → sāpekkho (s1-3)
#. VAR: patibaddhacitto → paṭibaddhacitto (bj, s2, s3, pts1) | patibandhacitto (mr)
msgctxt "an7.52:4.1"
msgid ""
"“Idha, sāriputta, ekacco sāpekho dānaṃ deti, patibaddhacitto dānaṃ deti, "
"sannidhipekho dānaṃ deti, ‘imaṃ pecca paribhuñjissāmī’ti dānaṃ deti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:4.2"
msgid ""
"So taṃ dānaṃ deti samaṇassa vā brāhmaṇassa vā annaṃ pānaṃ vatthaṃ yānaṃ "
"mālāgandhavilepanaṃ seyyāvasathapadīpeyyaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:4.3"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, sāriputta, dadeyya idhekacco evarūpaṃ dānan”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:4.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.61"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an7.52:5.1"
msgid ""
"“Tatra, sāriputta, yvāyaṃ sāpekho dānaṃ deti, patibaddhacitto dānaṃ deti, "
"sannidhipekho dānaṃ deti, ‘imaṃ pecca paribhuñjissāmī’ti dānaṃ deti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:5.2"
msgid ""
"So taṃ dānaṃ datvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā cātumahārājikānaṃ devānaṃ "
"sahabyataṃ upapajjati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:5.3"
msgid ""
"So taṃ kammaṃ khepetvā taṃ iddhiṃ taṃ yasaṃ taṃ ādhipaccaṃ āgāmī hoti āgantā "
"itthattaṃ. (1)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an7.52:6.1"
msgid ""
"Idha pana, sāriputta, ekacco na heva kho sāpekho dānaṃ deti, na "
"patibaddhacitto dānaṃ deti, na sannidhipekho dānaṃ deti, na ‘imaṃ pecca "
"paribhuñjissāmī’ti dānaṃ deti;"
msgstr ""

# Curiously, the text does not specify the results of giving in the abbreviated versions. It skips up to rebirth in the Brahma realm for the last one. Presumably each grade of giving would get you one level higher in the celestial hierarchy. The numbers work out, but the logic is dubious. Is giving because it is good less virtuous than doing so because of wanting to follow the example of some Vedic seers? There’s no comment on this in Comm, BB, or Hare.
msgctxt "an7.52:6.2"
msgid "api ca kho ‘sāhu dānan’ti dānaṃ deti … pe …. (2)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an7.52:7.1"
msgid "Napi ‘sāhu dānan’ti dānaṃ deti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:7.2"
msgid ""
"api ca kho ‘dinnapubbaṃ katapubbaṃ pitupitāmahehi na arahāmi porāṇaṃ "
"kulavaṃsaṃ hāpetun’ti dānaṃ deti … pe …. (3)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an7.52:8.1"
msgid ""
"Napi ‘dinnapubbaṃ katapubbaṃ pitupitāmahehi na arahāmi porāṇaṃ kulavaṃsaṃ "
"hāpetun’ti dānaṃ deti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:8.2"
msgid ""
"api ca kho ‘ahaṃ pacāmi, ime na pacanti, nārahāmi pacanto apacantānaṃ dānaṃ "
"adātun’ti dānaṃ deti … pe …. (4)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an7.52:9.1"
msgid ""
"Napi ‘ahaṃ pacāmi, ime na pacanti, nārahāmi pacanto apacantānaṃ dānaṃ adātun’"
"ti dānaṃ deti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:9.2"
msgid ""
"api ca kho ‘yathā tesaṃ pubbakānaṃ isīnaṃ tāni mahāyaññāni ahesuṃ, "
"seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:9.3"
msgid ""
"aṭṭhakassa vāmakassa vāmadevassa vessāmittassa yamadaggino aṅgīrasassa "
"bhāradvājassa vāseṭṭhassa kassapassa bhaguno, evaṃ me ayaṃ dānasaṃvibhāgo "
"bhavissatī’ti dānaṃ deti … pe …. (5)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.62"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an7.52:10.1"
msgid ""
"Napi ‘yathā tesaṃ pubbakānaṃ isīnaṃ tāni mahāyaññāni ahesuṃ, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:10.2"
msgid ""
"aṭṭhakassa vāmakassa vāmadevassa vessāmittassa yamadaggino aṅgīrasassa "
"bhāradvājassa vāseṭṭhassa kassapassa bhaguno, evaṃ me ayaṃ dānasaṃvibhāgo "
"bhavissatī’ti dānaṃ deti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:10.3"
msgid ""
"api ca kho ‘imaṃ me dānaṃ dadato cittaṃ pasīdati, attamanatā somanassaṃ "
"upajāyatī’ti dānaṃ deti … pe …. (6)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an7.52:11.1"
msgid ""
"Napi ‘imaṃ me dānaṃ dadato cittaṃ pasīdati, attamanatā somanassaṃ upajāyatī’"
"ti dānaṃ deti;"
msgstr ""

# See BB for the variant iti.
msgctxt "an7.52:11.2"
msgid "api ca kho cittālaṅkāracittaparikkhāraṃ dānaṃ deti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:11.3"
msgid ""
"So taṃ dānaṃ deti samaṇassa vā brāhmaṇassa vā annaṃ pānaṃ vatthaṃ yānaṃ "
"mālāgandhavilepanaṃ seyyāvasathapadīpeyyaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:11.4"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, sāriputta, dadeyya idhekacco evarūpaṃ dānan”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:11.5"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.63"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
#. VAR: na heva → naheva kho (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an7.52:12.1"
msgid "“Tatra, sāriputta, yvāyaṃ na heva sāpekho dānaṃ deti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:12.2"
msgid "na patibaddhacitto dānaṃ deti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:12.3"
msgid "na sannidhipekho dānaṃ deti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:12.4"
msgid "na ‘imaṃ pecca paribhuñjissāmī’ti dānaṃ deti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:12.5"
msgid "napi ‘sāhu dānan’ti dānaṃ deti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:12.6"
msgid ""
"napi ‘dinnapubbaṃ katapubbaṃ pitupitāmahehi na arahāmi porāṇaṃ kulavaṃsaṃ "
"hāpetun’ti dānaṃ deti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:12.7"
msgid ""
"napi ‘ahaṃ pacāmi, ime na pacanti, nārahāmi pacanto apacantānaṃ dānaṃ adātun’"
"ti dānaṃ deti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:12.8"
msgid ""
"napi ‘yathā tesaṃ pubbakānaṃ isīnaṃ tāni mahāyaññāni ahesuṃ, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:12.9"
msgid ""
"aṭṭhakassa vāmakassa vāmadevassa vessāmittassa yamadaggino aṅgīrasassa "
"bhāradvājassa vāseṭṭhassa kassapassa bhaguno, evaṃ me ayaṃ dānasaṃvibhāgo "
"bhavissatī’ti dānaṃ deti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:12.10"
msgid ""
"napi ‘imaṃ me dānaṃ dadato cittaṃ pasīdati, attamanatā somanassaṃ upajāyatī’"
"ti dānaṃ deti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:12.11"
msgid "api ca kho cittālaṅkāracittaparikkhāraṃ dānaṃ deti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:12.12"
msgid ""
"So taṃ dānaṃ datvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā brahmakāyikānaṃ devānaṃ "
"sahabyataṃ upapajjati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:12.13"
msgid ""
"So taṃ kammaṃ khepetvā taṃ iddhiṃ taṃ yasaṃ taṃ ādhipaccaṃ anāgāmī hoti "
"anāgantā itthattaṃ. (7)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "an7.52:13.1"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ kho, sāriputta, hetu ayaṃ paccayo yena midhekaccassa tādisaṃyeva dānaṃ "
"dinnaṃ na mahapphalaṃ hoti na mahānisaṃsaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an7.52:13.2"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ pana, sāriputta, hetu ayaṃ paccayo yena midhekaccassa tādisaṃyeva dānaṃ "
"dinnaṃ mahapphalaṃ hoti mahānisaṃsan”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an7.52:13.3"
msgid "Navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
